    "body": ">  For the first iteration it should treat the hard coded list the same as any nodes that have been connected to via discovery.\r\n\r\nCurrently, discovery populates a routing table and PeerPool picks random items from there to try and connect to, but it doesn't keep track of nodes it failed to connect to, so if we throw those static nodes in that routing table (which usually get pretty big quickly), there's a high probability that the PeerPool might never try to connect to any of those static nodes.",
